sorry if this seems clunky or rushed but like. im just so tired of aaron being painted as a 100% cold blooded killer
he isnt all black and white you know
summary: Ya’know one thing that busts my chops a bit is when people say that Aaron was going to kill Miles but had a change of heart last...
body:
Ya’know one thing that busts my chops a bit is when people say that Aaron was going to kill Miles but had a change of heart last minute/pulled down his mask so he wouldn’t have to look at his nephew’s face while he killed him

NO! HE WASNT!

Now I’m talking about the reveal

Can you

Look at this face right here

That is guilt. That is shock, and fear and guilt. He had no idea that that was Miles the whole time (and if you kinda analyze the running away in the house before, it seemed that he was even a little hesitant to kill him, though in the end he would do his job, he still knew that this was a kid behind the mask)

Now look at this

That’s the exact moment he pulls his mask back down. That’s not a killing stance. That is a stance of someone pulling away and letting go, surrendering to his nephew. That is a stance of someone who feels guilty and wanting to make things right. Even if it’ll take a lifetime. To explain everything, and be willing to do whatever it takes to make it up to him.

This is the face he has before he’s shot by Kingpin. Look at that. He was never planning to kill his nephew. He looks, like I said, guilty, and he even looks upset, and anguished. If he hadn’t died I 100% guarantee he would’ve been haunted by the fact that he nearly killed Miles for the rest of his life.

Aaron fucking loves his nephew probably more than himself. It’s pretty evident in their interactions in the beginning of the story that they have a really deep bond. Hell, Miles even says that Aaron is the only one he can talk to. Do you really think he’d kill someone whom he loves so much?

Please, full stop with this.

summary: I’ve been a fan of spider man for years. Been watching the cartoons since I was a kid, played the old insomniac PS1 games, and...
body:
I’ve been a fan of spider man for years. Been watching the cartoons since I was a kid, played the old insomniac PS1 games, and have recently been into the new movies and the spider-gwen comics. I’ve been looking around and I’m not finding anything that has Mary Jane as a significant character.

Can anyone recommend any comics where MJ is the protagonist or becomes a super-hero in her own right?
